<concept id="concept_lry_34g_xw">
    <title>Request a <ph
            conref="../Reusable_Content/ReusablePhrases.dita#concept_vhs_5tz_xp/DPM-short"/>
        Organization and User Account</title>
    <shortdesc>To register a <ph
            conref="../Reusable_Content/ReusablePhrases.dita#concept_vhs_5tz_xp/pName-long"/> with
            <ph conref="../Reusable_Content/ReusablePhrases.dita#concept_vhs_5tz_xp/DPM-LongOnly"/>,
        you must have a <ph
            conref="../Reusable_Content/ReusablePhrases.dita#concept_vhs_5tz_xp/DPM-short"/> user
        account within an organization.</shortdesc>
    <conbody>
        <p>A <ph conref="../Reusable_Content/ReusablePhrases.dita#concept_vhs_5tz_xp/DPM-short"/>
            organization groups all user accounts from an enterprise. All <ph
                conref="../Reusable_Content/ReusablePhrases.dita#concept_vhs_5tz_xp/pName-long"/>s,
            pipelines, jobs, and topologies added by any user in the organization belong to that
            organization. An organization typically includes multiple user accounts that perform
            different roles within <ph
                conref="../Reusable_Content/ReusablePhrases.dita#concept_vhs_5tz_xp/DPM-short"
            />.</p>
        <p>If you already have an organization defined for your enterprise, ask the organization
            administrator for a user account. If you donâ€™t have access to an organization, contact
            StreamSets with a request for a new organization.</p>
        <p>Your <ph conref="../Reusable_Content/ReusablePhrases.dita#concept_vhs_5tz_xp/DPM-short"/>
            user account must have the appropriate roles to register a <ph
                conref="../Reusable_Content/ReusablePhrases.dita#concept_vhs_5tz_xp/pName-long"/>.
        </p>
    </conbody>
</concept>
